#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:2
msgid "Administrator tool"
msgstr "Herramienta de administrador"

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:6
msgid "The applications eases the life of the site administrators."
msgstr "Las aplicaciones facilitan la vida de los administradores del sitio."

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:10
msgid "User management"
msgstr "Administración de usuario"

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:12
msgid ""
"A fully featured user listing view, providing a search and sorting "
"options, allows the administrator to have full control on its site users."
msgstr ""

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:15
msgid "The users can be sorted:"
msgstr "Los usuarios pueden ser ordenados:"

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:17
msgid "Alphabetically"
msgstr "Alfabéticamente"

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:18
msgid "By their state"
msgstr "Por su estado"

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:19
msgid "By creation date"
msgstr "Por fecha de creación"

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:20
msgid "By login date"
msgstr "Por fecha de inicio de sesión"

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:22
msgid ""
"Through this application it is possible to add a new user and control "
"their state."
msgstr ""

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:27
msgid "Screenshots"
msgstr "Capturas de pantallas"

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:30
#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:36
msgid "The app landing page"
msgstr "La página de inicio de la aplicación"

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:38
msgid ""
"It shows all the users sorted alphabetically and with the possibility to "
"search for users. If you have lots of users do not worry! The users are "
"paginated and will load automatically as you scroll the page."
msgstr ""

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:45
#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:51
msgid "The users sorted by their account status"
msgstr "Los usuario ordenados por su estatus de cuenta"

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:56
#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:62
msgid "The activate/deactivate user confirmation panel"
msgstr "El panel de confirmación de activar/deactivar usuario"

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:64
msgid ""
"On each row of the user listing there is a badge showing the user status."
" By clicking on it you will be redirected to a panel asking you to "
"confirm if you want to toggle the user state."
msgstr ""

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:71
#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:77
msgid "The create user panel"
msgstr "El panel de creación de usuario"

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:79
msgid ""
"By clicking the plus icon in the app landing page it is possible to add a"
" new user. The user will receive an email (be sure your mail setting in "
"the Plone control panel are ok) with a link to reset his password."
msgstr ""

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:87
msgid "How can I?"
msgstr "¿Como puedo yo?"

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:90
msgid "How can I delete a user?"
msgstr "¿Como puedo yo eliminar un usuario?"

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:92
msgid ""
"Deleting a user is discouraged in Quaive, because this could break the "
"\"social\" aspect of the intranet. Any content that a user has created is"
" suddenly without a connection to the creator. That is why in the "
"Administrator Tool, you can only disable a user to prevent further "
"logging in."
msgstr ""

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:94
msgid ""
"However, there might be a reason to really delete a users, e.g. if you "
"created a duplicate account. This is possible in the CMS "
"https://cms[yourname].quaivecloud.com/profiles/folder_contents."
msgstr ""

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:96
msgid ""
"In the root, click on \"Contents\", then on Profiles. This takes you "
"here: https://cms[yourname].quaivecloud.com/profiles/folder_contents."
msgstr ""

#: ../apps/administrator-tool/index.rst:98
msgid ""
"Locate the duplicate profile: just hover over the link to see the URL. "
"Tick the duplicate one, press Delete. Warning: for a new user who has not"
" created any content yet, this should be no problem. But deleting a user "
"this way who has created content already will lead to broken links."
msgstr ""

